    • populateActors

      public void populateActors(File actorsFile) throws ClassNotFoundException, SQLException, IOException, JSONSchemaException
      Fills out the actors table from values obtained from the parser. Also fill out the intermediate tables AwardWinningActor and Cast
      Parameters:
      actorsFile - the file which is going to be read, Since this calls the actorParser it handles if the file does not meet a valid schema
      Throws:
      ClassNotFoundException - if the driver cannot be loaded
      SQLException - if there is a problem introducing values because of bad SQL Code
      IOException - if there is a problem reading the file. This is thrown from the actorsParser method
      JSONSchemaException - if the passed file does not really meet

    • population

      public static String population(PopulateDB obj, File actorFile, File awardFile, File movieFile, File directorFile, File ratingsFile, File genreFile) throws JSONSchemaException
      Fills out all the tables by calling the different populate methods in a bulk. This is done for better testing and commodity
      Parameters:
      obj - the object what allows calling the different populate methods
      actorFile - file that contains the values for the actors table and its intermediate tables
      awardFile - the file that contains the values for the awards table
      movieFile - file that contains the values for the movies table and its intermediate tables
      directorFile - file that contains the values for the director table and its intermediate table
      ratingsFile - file that contains the values for the ratings table
      genreFile - file that contains the values for the genre table
      Returns:
      string that communicates the output of the operation
      Throws:
      JSONSchemaException - if any of the files do not meet the schema
